# Correct Example

> ⚠️ Warning: Physical or console access is required.

## Steps

### 1️⃣ Boot into GRUB
1. Reboot the system.
2. At the GRUB menu, select the kernel you want to boot.
3. Press `e` to edit the boot entry.
4. Append `rd.break` to the end of the linux line.

### 2️⃣ Remount filesystem
```bash
mount -o remount,rw /sysroot
chroot /sysroot



